msgid ""
"Install Klein for Ray and build your first bounded and streaming data "
"pipelines."
msgstr "安装 Klein for Ray，并构建第一个有界和流式数据管道。"

msgid "Get started with Klein for Ray"
msgstr "Klein for Ray 快速入门"

msgid ""
"This guide creates a bounded `DataStream`, executes it explicitly, and "
"shows how to submit a long-running pipeline."
msgstr "本指南将创建一个有界 `DataStream`，显式执行它，并演示如何提交长时间运行的管道。"

msgid "Install Klein"
msgstr "安装 Klein"

msgid ""
"Create an isolated Python environment and install Klein from the project "
"checkout:"
msgstr "创建隔离的 Python 环境，并从项目检出版本安装 Klein："

msgid ""
"Kafka, Iceberg, RocketMQ, Redis, RocksDB, and Serve are optional "
"integrations. Install only the extra required by the application, for "
"example `.[kafka]`, `.[iceberg]`, `.[rocketmq]`, `.[redis]`, "
"`.[rocksdb]`, or `.[serve]`. Use `.[all]` for an integration development "
"environment. RocketMQ also requires the native `librocketmq` runtime on "
"every worker."
msgstr ""
"Kafka、Iceberg、RocketMQ、Redis、RocksDB 和 Serve 均为可选集成。只需安装应用所需的 "
"extra，例如 `.[kafka]`、`.[iceberg]`、`.[rocketmq]`、`.[redis]`、`.[rocksdb]` 或 "
"`.[serve]`。集成开发环境请使用 `.[all]`。RocketMQ 还要求每个 worker 都具备原生 "
"`librocketmq` 运行时。"

msgid "Run a bounded pipeline"
msgstr "运行有界管道"

msgid ""
"A terminal operation such as `take_all()` registers a sink. Call `execute"
"(\"job-name\")` to run every registered sink in the bounded graph:"
msgstr "`take_all()` 等终结操作会注册 sink。调用 `execute(\"job-name\")` 以运行有界图中所有已注册的 sink："

msgid "The completed job handle returns these rows:"
msgstr "已完成的作业句柄会返回以下行："

msgid ""
"Klein creates a lazy graph through the registered terminal sinks. "
"`execute()` selects batch execution for the bounded source and lowers the"
" graph to Ray Data."
msgstr "Klein 通过已注册的终结 sink 创建惰性图。`execute()` 为有界源选择批处理执行，并将图下沉到 Ray Data。"

msgid "Read data with Ray Data"
msgstr "使用 Ray Data 读取数据"

msgid ""
"Source construction follows `ray.data`. Call a reader directly from "
"`ray.klein`, then choose Klein or Ray Data transformations:"
msgstr "源的构造方式遵循 `ray.data`。直接从 `ray.klein` 调用 reader，然后选择 Klein 或 Ray Data 转换："

msgid ""
"Klein forwards reader and Dataset arguments to the installed Ray version."
" See [Ray Data interoperability](ray-data-interop.md) for the execution "
"boundary and advanced adapters, or the [connector "
"catalog](connectors/index.md) to choose an input or output and review all"
" of its options."
msgstr ""
"Klein 会将 reader 和 Dataset 参数转发给已安装的 Ray 版本。有关执行边界和高级适配器，请参阅 [Ray Data "
"互操作性](ray-data-interop.md)；也可以通过[连接器目录](connectors/index.md) "
"选择输入或输出并查看其全部选项。"

msgid "Submit a dataflow"
msgstr "提交数据流"

msgid "Register one or more terminal sinks, then submit them together:"
msgstr "注册一个或多个终结 sink，然后将它们一并提交："

msgid ""
"`explain()` returns the dataflow plan without submitting it. `execute()` "
"returns a job handle that you can use to wait for completion or inspect "
"status."
msgstr "`explain()` 返回数据流计划，但不会提交它。`execute()` 返回作业句柄，可用来等待作业完成或检查状态。"

msgid ""
"Bounded sources complete after producing all records. Streaming sources, "
"such as Kafka or a custom `SourceFunction`, keep the job active until you"
" stop it or the source terminates."
msgstr "有界源生成全部记录后便会完成。Kafka 或自定义 `SourceFunction` 等流式源会让作业保持活动，直到用户将其停止或源终止。"

msgid ""
"The Kafka source emits the same raw byte schema as `ray.data.read_kafka`."
" It discovers new partitions while running, marks empty inputs idle for "
"watermark progress, and resumes from the next offsets stored in the "
"latest checkpoint. For bounded jobs, `write_kafka` uses Ray Data. For "
"streaming jobs, Klein owns a producer per sink subtask and waits for "
"Kafka delivery acknowledgements before advancing checkpoint and replay "
"watermarks. This provides at-least-once delivery: failures can replay a "
"message, so downstream consumers must tolerate duplicates when exactly-"
"once processing is required."
msgstr ""
"Kafka 源发出与 `ray.data.read_kafka` "
"相同的原始字节模式。它会在运行期间发现新分区，将空输入标记为空闲以推进水位线，并从最新检查点中存储的下一偏移量恢复。对于有界作业，`write_kafka`"
" 使用 Ray Data。对于流式作业，Klein 为每个 sink 子任务持有一个 producer，并在推进检查点和重放水位线前等待 "
"Kafka 交付确认。这提供至少一次交付：故障可能导致消息重放，因此在需要精确一次处理时，下游消费者必须能够容忍重复消息。"

msgid "Configure a pipeline"
msgstr "配置管道"

msgid ""
"Use a mapping, a `key=value` string, typed options, or `RAY_KLEIN_*` "
"environment variables. Explicit code takes precedence over environment "
"values:"
msgstr "可使用映射、`key=value` 字符串、类型化选项或 `RAY_KLEIN_*` 环境变量。代码中的显式配置优先于环境变量值："

msgid ""
"This example selects the optional RocksDB backend; install `.[rocksdb]` "
"first. The dependency-free default is `memory`."
msgstr "此示例选择可选的 RocksDB 后端；请先安装 `.[rocksdb]`。不依赖额外组件的默认后端是 `memory`。"

msgid ""
"See [Configure Klein](configuration.md) for precedence and value "
"conversion, then use the [configuration reference](configuration-"
"reference.md) to find every supported key, default, constraint, and "
"environment variable."
msgstr ""
"有关优先级和值转换，请参阅[配置 Klein](configuration.md)；随后可使用[配置参考](configuration-"
"reference.md) 查找所有受支持的键、默认值、约束和环境变量。"

msgid "Next steps"
msgstr "后续步骤"

msgid ""
"Read [Key concepts](key-concepts.md) to understand execution, state, "
"event time, and recovery."
msgstr "阅读[核心概念](key-concepts.md)，了解执行、状态、事件时间和恢复。"

msgid ""
"Build the [production streaming walkthrough](production-streaming.md) "
"when you are ready to connect Kafka, watermarks, state, checkpoints, and "
"transactional file output."
msgstr "准备好连接 Kafka、水位线、状态、检查点和事务型文件输出后，请完成[生产环境流处理实战](production-streaming.md)。"

msgid ""
"Check the [operator compatibility matrix](operator-compatibility.md) "
"before mixing Ray Data and native streaming operations."
msgstr "混用 Ray Data 与原生流式操作前，请查看[算子兼容性矩阵](operator-compatibility.md)。"

msgid ""
"Follow the [user guides](user-guides.md) to build stateful pipelines and "
"configure production storage."
msgstr "按照[用户指南](user-guides.md) 构建有状态管道并配置生产存储。"

#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Browse the {doc}`API reference <api/api>` for public methods and "
"configuration options."
msgstr "浏览 {doc}`API 参考 <api/api>`，了解公共方法和配置选项。"

